Clone a Call Center

To create more than one call center for a particular CTI adapter, you can clone an existing one. For example, if you already have a call center record for a Cisco IPCC Enterprise™ call center based in one location, you can clone that record for a Cisco IPCC Enterprise call center based in another location.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To view and clone a call center:	Manage Call Centers

To clone a call center:

1. From Setup, enter Call Centers in the Quick Find box, then select Call Centers.
2. Click the name of the call center that you want to clone.
3. Click Clone.
4. Make any additional changes to the new call center as necessary.
5. Click Save to save the new call center, or click Cancel to return to the All Call Centers page without saving the cloned call center.

NOTE If you have read-only access to a field, the value of that field isn’t carried over to the cloned record.
